ng> - Creating environments where everyone feels respected, valued, and able to fully participate, irrespective of their differences.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-56_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-57_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practices</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-60_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Equality Act 2010</strong> - This landmark legislation prohibits discrimination, harassment, and victimisation based on protected characteristics and requires organisations to promote equality and eliminate unlawful discrimination.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014</strong> - Regulation 9 requires providers to ensure that care is provided in a way that respects individuals' dignity and promotes their independence, rights, and choices.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Best practice guidance</strong> - Organisations such as Skills for Care and the Care Quality Commission offer guidance and resources to support the implementation of effective Equality and Diversity practices in Social Care settings.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-67_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Elevating_Social_Care_with_Inclusive_Practices_A_